n embedded key-value store seeded with the first event's ID) is sufficient; no real OS or network dependency. MOCK-HIDE: The dedup store can be a real in-process map or embedded DB; a spy on the mock queue confirms no second write occurred. LLM-DEP: None. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected — the dedup check is in-process state; an in-process seeded store catches the failure equally to a real external store.","test_description":"Send a valid signed request twice with the same event ID via in-process test client. After the first request, assert the mock queue write was called once. After the second request, assert the mock queue write was still called only once total. Assert the second response is still 200 (acknowledged) but the queue was not written.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.13,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When queue is full, handler returns 503 with Retry-After header","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure is at the boundary between the queue's 'full' signal and the handler's error-response logic. A unit test on the response-builder alone cannot confirm the handler correctly catches and translates the queue's full error. REAL-INFRA: A mock queue that throws or rejects with a 'queue full' error is fully sufficient; no real OS or network needed. MOCK-HIDE: The mock queue is the trigger for the error path; the assertion (503 + Retry-After header) is deterministic. LLM-DEP: None. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected — the queue's full condition can be deterministically injected via a mock stub.","test_description":"Configure the mock queue to reject writes with a 'capacity exceeded' error. Send a valid signed request via in-process test client. Assert the response status is 503. Assert the response includes a Retry-After header with a positive integer value.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_prob